threads.title: 820-3476-A - Not turning On
threads.message:
Macbook 820-3476-A


It doesn't turn ON.

However when plugged the power without battery the fan starts running at full speed.

By visual inspection. Nothing seems weird.

Reballed the SMC.. Still same beahvior

PPBUS = 15.56V
PP3V42 = 3.42V
PP5V_S5 = 5V
PP5V_S4 = 5V
PP5V_S0 = 5V
PPVRTC_G3H = 3.3V
PP1V05_S0 = 1.05V
PPVCC_S0_CPU = 0V

threads.title: 820-3476-A - Not turning On
threads.message:
If fan spins, board turns on!
Please, make difference between turn on and booting.

"PPBUS = 15.56V"
Are you sure about this, isn't 12.56V instead?

Inspect U1950 for corrosion.
Post voltage for its pins 1, 2, 7, 8.

threads.title: 820-3476-A - Not turning On
threads.message:
Yeah 12.56 my mistake.

U1950

1 0.102
2 0.810
7 0
8 3.43

Weird this ALL_SYS_PWRGD

threads.title: 820-3476-A - Not turning On
threads.message:
You've said to have 5V_S0.
Are you sure 3V3_S0 isn't there?

ALL_SYS_PWRGD must come high, before CPU core rail.
Remove Q8150 and check its level again.
